National Museum’s Facebook page July 29, 7.30pm www.facebook.com/ National.Museum.of.Singapore WHEN: ADMISSION: INFO: WHERE: WHEN: The Show Goes On...line: PiA’s Funny Way Of Life Singapore Heritage Festival: Digital Edition WHEN: ADMISSION: INFO: INFO: Revisit Taiwanese singer-songwriter PiA’s 2017 concert at the Esplanade, in which she performed songs from her first album, shared her sense of humour and optimism. Known for her jazz, pop-rock and funk ballads about everyday life, she and her band, known as the PiA band, were nominated for Best Musical Group at Taiwan’s 26th Golden Melody Awards. The concert was presented by in::music, Esplanade’s platform that nurtures and promotes emerging Mandopop artists and their original works. Beverly Morata & Mario Serio This year, get to know Tanjong Pagar, Pasir Ris and Kallang – from Tanjong Pagar’s early bustling rickshaw scene to tales of the resort holidays Singaporea­ns used to take in
Pasir Ris. You can also hone your pastry-making and belachanpo­unding skills with online workshops conducted by community partners.
www.heritagefe­stival.sg CHATg #1: All Heritage Is Intangible Vocalist Beverly Morata, a finalist in the first instalment of Singapore Idol, and jazz maestro Mario Serio will perform jazz favourites from composers such as Cole Porter,
Duke Ellington and the Gershwin brothers. The video will be live-streamed and available till
8pm on Sunday.
Tomorrow, 8pm
Free str.sg/JsCN Tropix Like It’s Hot: Summer Jam Virtual Music Festival In this webinar, heritage thought-leader Laurajane Smith will challenge the idea of heritage as primarily an object or site and instead explore it as a cultural process of meaning and memory-making.
View it at str.sg/JsCY Tomorrow, 2 - 4pm This online concert boasts more than 30 acts, including Autograf, a trio who play a mix of futuristic, tropical house; Dutch duo Firebeatz; and Australian duo Teddy Cream . There will also be guest speakers and interviews.
The concert is held in partnershi­p with the Makin’ Lemonade Fund, a relief organisati­on focusing on millennial­s and those from
Generation Z.
July 25, 4am - July 26, 12.30pm
